                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Hay, referring to his telegram of December 5, 1899, states that the
                    protocol, as forwarded with Mr. Tower’s dispatch No. 234, should contain
                    provision for the submission to the arbitrator of evidence which has been
                    presented in support of the claims.]</p>
            </div>
